Install express globally for ease of use.

$ npm install -g express

Create the base nodesite application.

$ express -e nodesite
$ cd nodesite
$ npm install

Check that we have the template application installed.

$ node app

Point the browser at localhost:3000 and see if the page exists.

Start a git repository for the project.

$ git init

Create a .gitignore file and add a line to omit the modules that are installed in the local module directory.

# Omit local modules.
node_modules/

